INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to enact the Local Law Enforcement Hate Crimes Prevention Act of 2007, which would provide federal assistance to states and local jurisdictions to prosecute hate crimes.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to reintroduce and pass the Local Law Enforcement Hate Crimes Prevention Act

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to suspending alternate side of the street parking regulations during snow storms.
EventItemMatterName: Suspending alternate side of the street parking regulations during snow storms.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to issuance of a certificate of completion for individuals working on supported scaffolds and design requirements for supported scaffolds.
EventItemMatterName: Issuance of a certificate of completion for individuals working on supported scaffolds and design requirements for supported scaffolds.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to civil penalties for violations of the littering law.
EventItemMatterName: Civil penalties for violations of the littering law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to limiting the issuance of notices of violations during certain times.
EventItemMatterName: Limiting the issuance of notices of violations during certain times.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of New York City to oppose the institution of any form of congestion pricing.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor of New York City to oppose the institution of any form of congestion pricing.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting New York State Assembly Bill A.5334, which would establish a program to coordinate the donation of excess food from school meal programs to voluntary food assistance programs.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a program to coordinate the donation of excess food from school meal programs to voluntary food assistance programs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Congress to reintroduce and the President of the United States to enact into law the “Religious Freedom Peace Tax Fund Act,” to affirm the religious freedom of taxpayers who are conscientiously opposed to participation in war and to provide that the income, estate or gift tax payments of such taxpayers be used for nonmilitary purposes.
EventItemMatterName: “Religious Freedom Peace Tax Fund Act”

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution commemorating the 39th Anniversary of the death of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. on April 4, 2007.
EventItemMatterName: Commemorating the 39th Anniversary of the death of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. on April 4, 2007.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution recognizing March as Colorectal Cancer Awareness Month in the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Recognizing March as Colorectal Cancer Awareness Month in the City of New York.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to inspection cycles for exterior walls.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that critical examinations of building facades for buildings greater than six stories in height take place on a five-year cycle starting from the year in which the building was erected.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass legislation to address the financial hardships placed upon New York residents who are members of the militia, national guard or armed services reserves.
EventItemMatterName: Address the financial hardships placed upon NY residents who are members of the militia, national guard or armed services reserves.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to consult with educators, parents, community leaders and other interested stakeholders regarding the recent school reforms, and to delay the implementation of these reforms until the potential impact has been fully assessed.
EventItemMatterName: School reforms, and to delay the implementation of these reforms until the potential impact has been fully assessed.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States federal government to preserve immediate and non-contingent Medicaid eligibility for children born in the United States to undocumented immigrants.
EventItemMatterName: US federal government to preserve immediate and non-contingent Medicaid eligibility for children born in the US to undocumented immigrants.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an owner’s duty to purchase and install radiator covers.
EventItemMatterName: An owner’s duty to purchase and install radiator covers.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the Governor of the State of New York to issue an Executive Order to the State Agencies under his control mandating the procurement of Recycled Plastic Lumber (RPL) where it is a viable alternative to natural or chemically treated wood and urging the State Legislature to enact legislation mandating municipalities to do the same.
EventItemMatterName: Mandating the procurement of Recycled Plastic Lumber (RPL) where it is a viable and potentially economically efficient alternative to natural or chemically treated wood.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to alteration permits.
EventItemMatterName: Alteration Permits

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to examination and application of plans.
EventItemMatterName: Examination and application of plans.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass legislation to increase the number of Family Court judges in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Increase the number of Family Court judges in New York City.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Congress to pass S. 453, the “Deceptive Practices and Voter Intimidation Prevention Act of 2007,” introduced by Senator Barack Obama, which prohibits deceptive practices in Federal elections.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass S. 453, the “Deceptive Practices and Voter Intimidation Prevention Act of 2007."

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to school bus safety.
EventItemMatterName: School bus safety.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, inrelation to the establishment of the Court-Livingston-Schermerhorn business improvement district.
EventItemMatterName: Court-Livingston-Schermerhorn Business Improvement District

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the Volunteer Ambulance Workers’ Benefit Law to include volunteer ambulance workers who render aid at the request of the City.
EventItemMatterName: Volunteer Ambulance Workers’ Benefit Law to include volunteer ambulance workers who render aid at the request of the City.
